By taking me

04:13.781 --> 04:19.052
to Dave & Buster's
for our anniversary?

04:19.053 --> 04:21.687
Aah!

04:21.689 --> 04:23.322
What?

04:23.324 --> 04:27.226
They called earlier to confirm.

04:27.228 --> 04:28.661
Ah, I forgot to cancel.

04:28.662 --> 04:31.396
We're-we're not actually going
to Dave & Buster's.

04:31.398 --> 04:33.966
Oh, thank God.

04:35.468 --> 04:38.771
But I seemed
on board though, right?

04:38.772 --> 04:41.808
For our anniversary, you, me,
and a group of our friends

04:41.809 --> 04:45.311
are gonna take a moonlit boat
tour of beautiful Lake Michigan

04:45.312 --> 04:48.680
with views of the city
we fell in love in.

04:48.682 --> 04:51.951
Get out of here.

04:51.952 --> 04:53.986
No, I will not.

04:53.987 --> 04:55.187
Oh, my God.

04:55.189 --> 04:56.322
I am blown away.

04:56.323 --> 04:58.957
And will you thank
whoever gave you that idea?

04:58.959 --> 05:01.127
It was Carl.

05:01.128 --> 05:02.528
But everything comes
with a price.

05:02.529 --> 05:05.497
He's singing "Isn't She Lovely"
for our first dance.

05:05.499 --> 05:07.733
Mike, do you think
it's really a good idea

05:07.734 --> 05:10.302
to have Carl and Victoria
at the same party?

05:10.304 --> 05:13.238
Well, not really. But what am I
supposed to do, uninvite him?

05:14.674 --> 05:16.775
Aw, come on!

05:16.777 --> 05:18.577
Well, what are we supposed
to do?

05:18.578 --> 05:21.881
I mean, the two of them?
Plus alcohol? On a boat?

05:21.882 --> 05:24.917
Did you not see
<i>The Poseidon Adventure?</i>

05:24.918 --> 05:26.485
We're gonna be upside down

05:26.486 --> 05:30.255
and climbing up a Christmas tree
before we know it.

05:30.257 --> 05:31.990
He was my best man.

05:31.992 --> 05:33.525
She's my sister.

05:33.527 --> 05:35.828
(sighs) Mol, you just don't
understand the kind of position

05:35.829 --> 05:37.062
you're gonna put me in.

05:37.063 --> 05:38.196
I do.

05:38.198 --> 05:39.465
It's an awful one.

05:39.466 --> 05:41.267
But tell him that we'll do
something together,

05:41.268 --> 05:42.934
just the three of us.

05:42.936 --> 05:45.937
Dave & Buster's?

05:45.939 --> 05:48.473
Yeah. Just the two of you.

05:48.475 --> 05:51.409
Yeah. Go.

05:54.380 --> 05:56.682
♪ Isn't sh... ♪

05:56.683 --> 05:58.417
(clears throat)
♪ Isn't... ♪

05:58.418 --> 05:59.384
(clears throat)

05:59.385 --> 06:04.121
♪ Isn't-isn't she lovely. ♪

06:04.123 --> 06:06.791
Hey, don't worry.
I'll be ready when we set sail.

06:06.793 --> 06:08.694
Yeah.

06:08.695 --> 06:10.895
Listen, Carl, um...
Mm-hmm.

06:12.731 --> 06:15.167
You remember
when you were picking players

06:15.168 --> 06:16.835
for the precinct
softball team,

06:16.836 --> 06:20.905
and when you didn't pick me, you
asked me to take it like a man?

06:20.907 --> 06:22.774
Mm-hmm. That was right
before you ripped up home plate

06:22.775 --> 06:24.141
and threw it at my head.

06:24.143 --> 06:29.146
But eventually I understood,
'cause it was good for the team.

06:29.148 --> 06:30.348
It was good for you, too.

06:30.349 --> 06:32.017
I mean, you may be built
like Babe Ruth,

06:32.018 --> 06:33.818
but you play like Dr. Ruth.

06:33.820 --> 06:35.787
Ha-ha! Dr. Ruth.

06:35.788 --> 06:36.788
That's a good one.

06:36.789 --> 06:39.056
You can't come to the party.

06:39.058 --> 06:41.659
Excuse me, what?

06:41.661 --> 06:45.497
Molly and I...
especially Molly...

06:45.498 --> 06:47.699
think it's a good idea
that you don't go

06:47.700 --> 06:49.333
since Victoria's
gonna be there.

06:49.335 --> 06:51.303
H-Hold on now. If you're talking
about what happened yesterday,

06:51.304 --> 06:52.570
that was not my fault.

06:52.571 --> 06:54.539
Okay, you heard her
when she walked in there.

06:54.540 --> 06:56.541
(mocking):
"Hello."

06:56.542 --> 06:58.676
I'm supposed to ignore all that?

06:58.678 --> 07:00.578
Well, look, I'm sorry.
You're out!

07:00.579 --> 07:02.280
I can't believe what I'm hearing.
(sighs)

07:02.281 --> 07:04.883
I basically introduced you two,
made you ask her out,

07:04.884 --> 07:06.451
and this whole party is my idea.

07:06.452 --> 07:08.051
Without me,
there is no Mike and Molly!

07:08.053 --> 07:09.554
I know.

07:09.555 --> 07:11.756
And I'm asking you,
as my best friend,

07:11.757 --> 07:14.691
please just let this one go.

07:14.693 --> 07:16.394
(sighs)

07:16.395 --> 07:18.395
Is that what you really want?

07:18.397 --> 07:19.998
No!

07:19.999 --> 07:23.667
But it's what
I need you to do.

07:23.669 --> 07:25.136
All right.

07:25.137 --> 07:26.837
Consider it done.

07:26.839 --> 07:30.141
Thank you.
You're a good friend.

07:30.142 --> 07:31.675
(sighs)

07:33.511 --> 07:35.713
(sniffles)

07:35.714 --> 07:38.648
(voice breaking):
♪ Isn't she lovely ♪

07:40.518 --> 07:41.853
(sniffles)

07:41.854 --> 07:45.822
♪ Isn't she wonderful... ♪

07:47.892 --> 07:50.228
Okay, not that
it's a competition,

07:50.229 --> 07:54.531
but I call Mike's anniversary
cruise, and I raise it with...

07:54.533 --> 07:56.000
this. Ta-da!

07:56.001 --> 07:57.200
Oh, my God.

07:57.202 --> 07:59.537
It's beautiful!

07:59.538 --> 08:01.371
What the hell is it?

08:01.373 --> 08:03.507
It's a window
into our relationship.

08:03.508 --> 08:04.842
I mean, these are the tickets

08:04.843 --> 08:06.643
from the first Cubs game
we ever saw.

08:06.645 --> 08:07.978
This is our wedding invitation.

08:07.979 --> 08:10.915
This is an actual page
out of Mike's police notebook

08:10.916 --> 08:12.448
when he first asked me out.

08:12.450 --> 08:15.752
Oh, he's so lucky
you're a hoarder.

08:15.754 --> 08:16.887
I'm not a hoarder.

08:16.888 --> 08:21.024
I'm a romantic
with hoarding tendencies.

08:21.026 --> 08:22.760
I can't believe you and Mike
have been married

08:22.761 --> 08:24.894
for three years already.
I know.

08:24.896 --> 08:27.030
And I can remember
our first date.

08:27.032 --> 08:29.565
Oh, I was so sick.
I got hopped up on liquor

08:29.567 --> 08:32.467
and cough syrup,
and I threw up all over his car.

08:32.470 --> 08:34.102
And he asked you
on a second date.

08:34.105 --> 08:36.639
That's when I knew I had him.

08:36.640 --> 08:40.110
It's hard to find
something special like that.

08:40.111 --> 08:43.813
But when you do,
hold on to it.

08:43.815 --> 08:44.815
Yeah.

08:44.816 --> 08:46.516
Oh, sweetie.

08:46.517 --> 08:48.951
You have so
much to offer.

08:48.953 --> 08:50.220
Thanks, Mom.

08:50.221 --> 08:52.555
Any man would be
lucky to have you.

08:52.557 --> 08:54.457
Or woman.

08:56.493 --> 08:58.228
Now, my friend Janice
has a daughter.

08:58.229 --> 09:00.163
Very successful
pediatrician.

09:00.164 --> 09:02.299
At least have coffee.

09:02.300 --> 09:03.666
See where it goes.

09:03.668 --> 09:06.336
Might as well.

09:06.337 --> 09:08.237
Couldn't hurt. Yeah.

09:13.310 --> 09:14.944
Ramirez!

09:14.946 --> 09:15.912
So glad you could make it.

09:15.913 --> 09:17.413
We're upstairs
on the Topaz Deck.

09:17.415 --> 09:19.282
All right. Open bar?
How long have you known me?

09:19.283 --> 09:20.750
Long enough to
bring my own flask.

09:20.751 --> 09:22.017
Attaboy.

09:22.019 --> 09:24.019
Hello, Michael!

09:24.021 --> 09:25.422
Aw, Nana.

09:25.423 --> 09:27.123
(chuckles)
Mmm.

09:27.124 --> 09:28.792
Hey, thank you so much
for coming.

09:28.793 --> 09:31.628
I hope you understand
why I couldn't invite Carl.

09:31.629 --> 09:33.997
Of course I do!
This is your night.

09:33.998 --> 09:35.999
And we all know what
Carl can be like.

09:36.000 --> 09:39.635
A grown-up party is no place
for a 12-year-old girl.

09:41.371 --> 09:42.471
SAMUEL:
Ah.

09:42.473 --> 09:43.473
Congratulations.

09:43.474 --> 09:45.274
Thank you.

09:47.143 --> 09:49.112
Seriously? A life vest?

09:49.113 --> 09:51.980
I'm sorry, I thought
we were on a boat.

09:53.149 --> 09:54.751
Happy anniversary, Mike.

09:54.752 --> 09:56.151
Two tickets to <i> Wicked.</i>

09:56.153 --> 09:57.453
Wow, hey, thanks, Harry.

09:57.454 --> 09:59.187
Molly's been wanting
to see that show.

09:59.189 --> 10:00.189
Oh.

10:00.190 --> 10:01.124
Sure, Molly.

10:01.125 --> 10:03.625
Yeah, I can see it
another time.

10:06.029 --> 10:07.797
This is a
beautiful venue.

10:07.798 --> 10:09.532
Yeah.
You really went all out.

10:09.533 --> 10:10.900
High-class,
all the way.

10:10.901 --> 10:12.467
It's a cash bar,
deal with it.

10:16.072 --> 10:17.673
Carl, what the hell
are you doing here?

10:17.674 --> 10:19.708
You promised me you weren't coming.
I did.

10:19.710 --> 10:21.509
But time has passed,
and things have changed.

10:21.511 --> 10:22.544
Who's this?

10:22.546 --> 10:24.213
Allow me to introduce you
to Stephanie.

10:24.214 --> 10:25.548
I pulled her off Craigslist.

10:25.549 --> 10:26.748
Hi.

10:29.619 --> 10:30.953
Please don't do this.

10:30.954 --> 10:32.321
I'm not doing anything
but enjoying

10:32.322 --> 10:33.956
a moonlit cruise
on Lake Michigan.

10:33.957 --> 10:35.491
And until we cross
into Canadian waters,

10:35.492 --> 10:37.492
this is still a free country.

10:37.494 --> 10:39.928
You know what's gonna happen
when Victoria spots you?

10:39.930 --> 10:41.931
Well, I don't know exactly,
but for the amount of money

10:41.932 --> 10:43.865
I paid on Stephanie,
I hope her head explodes.

10:47.903 --> 10:49.605
I see the entertainment
has arrived.

10:49.606 --> 10:50.905
(groans)

10:50.907 --> 10:54.442
Eight dollars for rum and Coke
suddenly seems like a bargain.

