11:09.315 --> 11:10.916
This is so romantic.

11:10.918 --> 11:13.553
You're lucky you got somebody
to share this with, Mom.

11:13.554 --> 11:15.655
Aw, honey, I know
you're disappointed,

11:15.656 --> 11:17.589
but you're gonna find somebody.

11:17.591 --> 11:19.391
Probably when you
least expect it.

11:19.393 --> 11:21.361
Look at your mother and me.

11:21.362 --> 11:23.730
Who knew a sloppy drunken
one-night stand

11:23.731 --> 11:25.398
would turn into forever?

11:25.399 --> 11:27.267
Not me, that's for sure.

11:27.268 --> 11:30.403
I woke up next to this one and
thought, "What have I done""

11:30.404 --> 11:31.704
(chuckles)

11:31.705 --> 11:34.072
"And who still has a water bed""

11:34.074 --> 11:36.975
Say what you want,
but that bed did half the work.

11:37.810 --> 11:40.146
Point is, love is tricky.

11:40.147 --> 11:41.713
You can't go looking for it.

11:41.715 --> 11:43.583
Then how am I gonna find it?

11:43.584 --> 11:46.284
You don't.
It finds you.

11:47.787 --> 11:49.788
Is it here now?

11:49.790 --> 11:52.091
It was, till you just asked.

11:52.092 --> 11:54.994
Now it's gone again,
till you forget about it.

11:54.995 --> 11:57.262
Have you not heard
a word we've said?

11:58.097 --> 12:00.298
This is all very confusing.

12:00.300 --> 12:01.300
Exactly.

12:01.301 --> 12:02.467
That's love.

12:03.936 --> 12:05.905
Three years married.

12:05.906 --> 12:09.608
That's right around the time
Mike's dad first cheated on me.

12:09.609 --> 12:12.678
You sure you don't want to save
that story for your toast?

12:12.679 --> 12:14.546
Mm.

12:14.548 --> 12:16.048
I should've known
something was up

12:16.049 --> 12:18.083
when he switched
to colored underwear.

12:18.084 --> 12:20.019
I guess what I'm saying is

12:20.020 --> 12:23.788
Mike knows the warning signs,
so watch your step.

12:23.790 --> 12:25.623
Hey, Ma.

12:25.625 --> 12:28.159
Check her underwear
to see what color it is.

12:30.963 --> 12:32.598
Listen...
No, you listen.

12:32.599 --> 12:34.967
You did it... this
party is amazing.

12:34.968 --> 12:36.635
And the bartender
knows I'm the bride,

12:36.636 --> 12:38.270
so I keep getting
free drinks.

12:38.271 --> 12:39.705
(laughs)

12:39.706 --> 12:41.173
Maybe you want to take it easy.

12:41.174 --> 12:43.107
We might have to keep
our wits about us.

12:43.109 --> 12:44.743
Oh, no.

12:44.744 --> 12:47.713
Is this some kind of
murder-mystery cruise?

12:47.714 --> 12:50.782
Mike, you were
doing so well.

12:50.784 --> 12:52.383
No, Carl's on the boat.

12:52.385 --> 12:53.684
What?
And he brought a date.

12:53.686 --> 12:55.420
What?
And I dropped my phone in the toilet,

12:55.421 --> 12:58.022
but Carl is the main problem.

12:58.024 --> 12:59.524
Well, you got to
get him out of here

12:59.525 --> 13:02.261
before Victoria sees him.
We're in the middle of a lake.

13:02.262 --> 13:03.661
What do you want me to do?
Push him overboard?

13:03.663 --> 13:05.030
There are a lot of
boats out there.

13:05.031 --> 13:06.597
Somebody's gonna
pick him up.

13:06.599 --> 13:08.533
Molly.
Fine.

13:08.534 --> 13:11.569
Give him a flashlight
and a whistle.

13:12.504 --> 13:14.372
Hey, Harry.

13:14.373 --> 13:15.707
Have you seen Victoria?

13:15.708 --> 13:17.174
No, I have not.

13:17.176 --> 13:19.543
And you're not supposed
to be here.

13:19.545 --> 13:21.947
Shouldn't you be floating out
in the darkness or somewhere,

13:21.948 --> 13:23.681
waiting for a ship to hit you?

13:23.683 --> 13:27.885
Haven't you hurt
enough people today?

13:30.088 --> 13:31.589
Charmed.

13:33.458 --> 13:35.794
You know something, it might be
the three margaritas,

13:35.795 --> 13:37.695
but I'm feeling much better.

13:37.696 --> 13:39.029
Aw, see?

13:39.031 --> 13:41.800
I don't know why they say
alcohol's a depressant.

13:41.801 --> 13:43.134
It fixes everything.

13:43.135 --> 13:44.436
Mm-hmm.

13:44.437 --> 13:45.570
Listen, Victoria.

13:45.571 --> 13:47.004
We-we may have a
bit of a situation.

13:47.006 --> 13:48.939
(Carl whoops,
dance music playing)

13:49.974 --> 13:51.942
(grunting rhythmically)

13:52.777 --> 13:54.812
(whoops)

13:54.814 --> 13:57.247
I'm sorry, he wasn't
supposed to come.

13:57.249 --> 13:59.250
Don't worry, I'll go
get rid of the two of them.

13:59.251 --> 14:00.585
No, you won't.

14:00.586 --> 14:02.052
I'll handle this.

14:02.054 --> 14:03.521
Ah, that's my girl.

14:03.522 --> 14:05.857
Get her to the ground,
put her in a camel clutch.

14:05.858 --> 14:07.225
End this quick
so we can get back

14:07.226 --> 14:08.792
to your sister's
nice party.

14:13.297 --> 14:15.532
Hey, Carl.

14:15.534 --> 14:19.970
I hope you have a wonderful
time at the party.

14:21.472 --> 14:23.841
See, that's how
we Flynn girls do it.

14:23.842 --> 14:25.476
Pure class.

14:25.477 --> 14:26.977
Jackass.

14:28.312 --> 14:30.247
Unbelievable.

14:32.450 --> 14:34.618
Ah, best drink ever.

14:40.591 --> 14:43.227
Okay, everybody,
come on, gather round.

14:43.228 --> 14:45.829
It's time for Mike
to open his present.

14:45.831 --> 14:47.998
Been wanting to get you
something that, you know,

14:47.999 --> 14:50.501
is from the heart and shows you
how much I love you.

14:50.502 --> 14:52.202
Aw, thank you, sweetie.

14:52.204 --> 14:54.872
All right, it's...

14:54.873 --> 14:57.207
an old window!

14:57.208 --> 14:58.509
I love it.

14:58.510 --> 15:00.143
Turn it over.
Over.

15:01.245 --> 15:02.580
Aw...

15:02.581 --> 15:04.248
It's stuff
from our life together.

15:04.249 --> 15:06.083
Yeah, Cubbies tickets.

15:06.084 --> 15:08.118
And, oh, there's the
"Do Not Disturb" sign

15:08.119 --> 15:09.586
from that hotel
where we first...

15:09.587 --> 15:11.921
Okay.
Okay, a lot of good memories.

15:11.923 --> 15:13.490
You like it?

15:13.491 --> 15:14.491
I love it.

15:14.492 --> 15:15.526
And I love you.

15:15.527 --> 15:17.494
I love you, too.

15:17.495 --> 15:18.528
All right.

15:18.530 --> 15:21.498
I would like to
say a few words.

15:21.499 --> 15:22.999
Oh, thanks.

15:25.135 --> 15:27.770
Four years, three months
and two days ago,

15:27.772 --> 15:31.808
I had no idea who the hell
I was or where I was going.

15:31.809 --> 15:34.912
And one day later,
all of that changed.

15:34.913 --> 15:36.513
'Cause I met a girl.

15:36.514 --> 15:40.082
And her only flaw
was her taste in men.

15:40.084 --> 15:41.450
(laughter)

15:41.452 --> 15:44.153
And I thank God
for that every day.

15:44.155 --> 15:46.456
I hope everyone here
is lucky enough

15:46.457 --> 15:50.093
to feel the way I feel at
least once in their life.

15:50.094 --> 15:52.329
Here is to love.

15:52.330 --> 15:54.397
ALL:
Aw...

15:54.398 --> 15:55.931
(applause)

16:00.403 --> 16:02.405
Did you have the
garlic prawns?

16:02.406 --> 16:03.973
No.
Good.

16:08.678 --> 16:10.714
Uh, as you probably
know by now,

16:10.715 --> 16:12.682
I did have the garlic prawns.

16:12.683 --> 16:15.184
But I sensed
this was my moment.

16:15.186 --> 16:17.619
Well, I'd hate to catch
what he just gave you.

16:17.621 --> 16:18.988
Don't worry,
uh, I'm very clean.

16:18.989 --> 16:21.390
No one has touched me
in three years.

16:21.392 --> 16:23.625
Well, let's
change that.

16:23.627 --> 16:24.860
Hey, get off
of her, man!

16:24.862 --> 16:26.496
Hey, hey, hey,
that's enough, Carl.

16:26.497 --> 16:28.331
Come here, come here.
What is wrong with you?

16:28.332 --> 16:30.832
Let go of me, man! Got nothing to do with you.
Hey, hey!

16:30.834 --> 16:32.901
(splash)

16:34.737 --> 16:35.971
You happy?!

16:35.973 --> 16:37.372
Now, how is this my fault?

16:37.374 --> 16:39.809
How is this your fault?
Because you made it about you.

16:39.810 --> 16:42.911
You're selfish, you're a baby,
and you're a crappy friend!

16:42.913 --> 16:44.247
Oh, I'm a crappy
friend, huh?

16:44.248 --> 16:45.581
None of this
would have happened

16:45.582 --> 16:46.882
if you just invited me,
but you didn't.

16:46.884 --> 16:49.252
You chose them over me
like you always do.

16:49.253 --> 16:51.353
Well, Victoria's family.

16:51.355 --> 16:53.256
Yeah, I thought I was family.

16:53.257 --> 16:55.323
Honestly, I don't know
what you are right now.

16:55.325 --> 16:57.392
Mike, it's okay.

16:57.394 --> 16:59.428
No, it's not.
He ruined everything.

16:59.429 --> 17:02.031
All our memories are at the
bottom of Lake Michigan.

17:02.032 --> 17:04.400
Hey, we'll make more, okay?

17:04.401 --> 17:06.402
We don't need a bunch
of stuff in an old window

17:06.403 --> 17:07.636
to prove what we've got.

17:07.637 --> 17:11.272
Come on, let the bride
get you a drink.

17:14.510 --> 17:16.444
So was all that just...?

17:16.445 --> 17:18.680
Okay, that's
what I thought.

17:30.657 --> 17:32.424
I haven't seen Carl yet.

17:32.426 --> 17:34.394
No,<i> he's</i> apologizing this time,

17:34.395 --> 17:37.430
and he'd better have a scone
in his hand when he does it.

17:37.431 --> 17:39.299
Hey, uh, what do you say
this weekend,

17:39.300 --> 17:41.634
we go down to that little hotel
and see if we can't

17:41.635 --> 17:45.138
earn ourselves another
"Do Not Disturb" sign?

17:45.139 --> 17:47.173
And Dave & Buster's?

17:47.174 --> 17:48.808
God, I love you.

17:48.809 --> 17:50.476
All right,
I'll talk to you later.

17:50.477 --> 17:52.711
Okay, love you, bye.

17:52.713 --> 17:54.913
Hey, Biggs.

17:55.982 --> 17:57.516
Ramirez, what are you doing?

17:57.518 --> 17:59.385
Oh, you didn't hear?
Carl requested a transfer.

17:59.386 --> 18:01.754
He already cleared
his locker out.

18:01.755 --> 18:03.756
What are you
talking about?

18:03.757 --> 18:05.223
I'm your new partner.

18:05.225 --> 18:06.826
Buckle up, big guy.

18:06.827 --> 18:09.161
I've got rules in my squad car.

